Architecture plan for Issue #153: Remove composer headings/outer box and make the input an auto-resizing textarea

Current structure:
- frontend/src/App.tsx contains the NetworkPage composition, including the network composer section and the MessageComposer React component.
- frontend/src/styles.css contains the Tailwind @apply component classes for the network layout and message composer presentation.
- shared/src/messages.ts defines message DTOs; no schema or shared type changes are expected for this UI-only issue.
- backend/ exposes the existing /api/messages endpoint; no backend changes are needed because message posting semantics remain unchanged.

Issue dependency plan:
- There is only one implementation issue in this batch, so there are no cross-issue dependencies.
- The change should preserve the existing MessageComposer state, validation, rate-limit handling, POST /api/messages payload, success callback, and disabled behavior.
- The network composer section title ID will be removed with its visible heading, so the section should use aria-label="Network message composer" instead of aria-labelledby.

Key design decisions:
- In frontend/src/App.tsx, remove the composer heading block containing the "Signal composer" kicker and "Broadcast to the network" title from NetworkPage.
- Replace the single-line <input> in MessageComposer with a <textarea rows={2}> so user text can span multiple lines while retaining maxLength, disabled, placeholder, id, value, and submit behavior.
- Add a textarea ref plus a small resize helper that sets height to auto and then to scrollHeight whenever the message body changes. This lets the field grow and shrink automatically as content is typed or cleared.
- In frontend/src/styles.css, strip the outer panel treatment from .tlhn-message-composer by removing border/background/padding/shadow styling and neutralizing the hater/lover border variants.
- Update .tlhn-message-input styling for textarea ergonomics: at least two rows high, vertical padding, leading, hidden overflow, and no manual resize handle, while retaining focus accents and disabled styles.
- Verify with the frontend typecheck/build and any available test command after implementation.
